520
00:32:06,391 --> 00:32:08,993
Terrorists.

521
00:32:08,994 --> 00:32:11,662
You actually prefer
the term "terrorist"?

522
00:32:11,663 --> 00:32:16,000
We terrorize foreigners
with guns and threats.

523
00:32:16,001 --> 00:32:19,403
Terrorism implies
that there's certain...

524
00:32:19,404 --> 00:32:21,539
it's for
some ideological cause,

525
00:32:21,540 --> 00:32:23,240
<i>ot just mere profit.</i>

526
00:32:23,241 --> 00:32:25,042
That is why it intrigues me.

527
00:32:25,043 --> 00:32:28,646
The media reserves the word
"terrorist" only for Arabs.

528
00:32:28,647 --> 00:32:30,514
Why do I deserve
special treatment?

529
00:32:30,515 --> 00:32:32,650
Why do you want to get
lumped in with fanatics?

530
00:32:32,651 --> 00:32:34,451
Ask yourself.

531
00:32:34,452 --> 00:32:35,386
What does the Middle East have
that Somalia does not?

532
00:32:39,991 --> 00:32:41,525
So, what you're
telling me is

533
00:32:41,526 --> 00:32:43,661
whenever we really want
to really scare our audience

534
00:32:43,662 --> 00:32:45,262
we pull out
the "terrorist" card

535
00:32:45,263 --> 00:32:47,998
to protect our interests
in the Middle East?

536
00:32:47,999 --> 00:32:49,700
But, if one
were to waste it

537
00:32:49,701 --> 00:32:52,536
on something like Somalia
which doesn't have any money?

538
00:32:52,537 --> 00:32:55,139
What, the word somehow
loses its luster?

539
00:32:55,140 --> 00:32:59,343
- That's ridiculous.
- Let's us speak off the record.

540
00:32:59,344 --> 00:33:02,146
Take your microphone off.

541
00:33:02,147 --> 00:33:03,080
Yeah, I'm with you.

542
00:33:04,349 --> 00:33:05,616
Shit, I just lost them.

543
00:33:05,617 --> 00:33:07,751
What do you mean
you lost them?

544
00:33:07,752 --> 00:33:10,087
Oh, shit, you think
they figured it out?

545
00:33:10,088 --> 00:33:12,356
I don't even,
I don't understand...

546
00:33:15,193 --> 00:33:17,494
Soon, I am going to ask
for money

547
00:33:20,765 --> 00:33:22,533
for my own ideological cause,

548
00:33:22,534 --> 00:33:26,537
but I guarantee you
that makes no difference

549
00:33:26,538 --> 00:33:28,505
to your terrified friends
back there.

550
00:33:28,506 --> 00:33:32,509
Fear is fear.

551
00:33:32,510 --> 00:33:36,247
Respectfully, I disagree.

552
00:33:36,248 --> 00:33:39,350
See, if all you want is money,
we can arrange for that,

553
00:33:39,351 --> 00:33:40,718
we can make an exchange.

554
00:33:40,719 --> 00:33:42,586
But if what you want to do

555
00:33:42,587 --> 00:33:45,322
is convert or kill
all the infidels

556
00:33:45,323 --> 00:33:47,591
there's no room
to bargain there.

557
00:33:47,592 --> 00:33:49,193
So, you are saying...

558
00:33:49,194 --> 00:33:50,728
because I'm just
a greedy negro,

559
00:33:50,729 --> 00:33:52,329
your friends
aren't scared of me?

560
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:54,064
I didn't say that.

561
00:33:54,065 --> 00:33:57,067
We're just more familiar
with your motives.

562
00:33:59,371 --> 00:34:01,372
Are you?

563
00:34:01,373 --> 00:34:03,474
Yes.

564
00:34:03,475 --> 00:34:04,642
We can put this to the test.

565
00:34:08,647 --> 00:34:11,649
If the majority of your friends
agree with you,

566
00:34:11,650 --> 00:34:13,784
that the motives
behind my actions

567
00:34:13,785 --> 00:34:16,520
determine how scared
they are of me,

568
00:34:16,521 --> 00:34:19,390
I will release you all
immediately.

569
00:34:19,391 --> 00:34:21,792
- You mean that?
- But...

570
00:34:21,793 --> 00:34:24,662
if more of them agree
with me,

571
00:34:24,663 --> 00:34:26,263
that fear is fear,

572
00:34:26,264 --> 00:34:29,133
regardless of motive,

573
00:34:29,134 --> 00:34:30,467
I will kill you.

574
00:34:31,770 --> 00:34:34,738
It's not a true belief,

575
00:34:36,341 --> 00:34:39,610
unless you're
willing to die for it.

576
00:34:39,611 --> 00:34:42,079
Is it a problem with the
receiver or the microphone?

577
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:44,415
Put that away,
he's coming.

578
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:53,357
What?

579
00:34:53,358 --> 00:34:55,125
- Go with him.
- Why?

580
00:34:55,126 --> 00:34:56,794
He wants you
to go with him.

581
00:34:56,795 --> 00:34:59,663
- Fuck's sake, again, what?
- Just do what he wants, Kane.

582
00:35:02,534 --> 00:35:05,536
Just so you know,
your mic's not on.

583
00:35:07,305 --> 00:35:07,438
Sit.

584
00:35:11,443 --> 00:35:15,579
Kane...

585
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:17,581
would you fear these men more

586
00:35:17,582 --> 00:35:19,717
if they hijacked this plane,
in, let's say,

587
00:35:19,718 --> 00:35:20,718
in the name of religion more
than just pure financial gain?

588
00:35:25,190 --> 00:35:27,858
What's the difference?

589
00:35:27,859 --> 00:35:30,728
You know, either way
they're psychopaths.

590
00:35:30,729 --> 00:35:32,296
Yeah, Kane got it back.

591
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:34,298
What do they want?
What are they saying?

592
00:35:34,299 --> 00:35:36,166
Hold on one second.

593
00:35:36,167 --> 00:35:37,701
What do they have him
doing there?

594
00:35:37,702 --> 00:35:39,703
So, this man standing here
is a psychopath?

595
00:35:39,704 --> 00:35:44,174
Yeah, that's what I said.

596
00:35:44,175 --> 00:35:47,177
What, does he have
some sob story

597
00:35:47,178 --> 00:35:48,445
to justify his actions?

598
00:35:48,446 --> 00:35:49,847
I'm sure it's very good.

599
00:35:49,848 --> 00:35:53,317
Thank you. You may go.

600
00:35:53,318 --> 00:35:54,585
What, that's it?

601
00:35:54,586 --> 00:35:55,652
Well, if I'm a psychopath,

602
00:35:55,653 --> 00:35:58,188
do you really want
to stick around?

603
00:35:58,189 --> 00:36:00,591
Thank you, Kane.

604
00:36:07,532 --> 00:36:10,501
1-0.

605
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:18,942
You really called him
a "psychopath"?

606
00:36:18,943 --> 00:36:20,778
Seriously?

607
00:36:20,779 --> 00:36:22,513
Oh, God.

608
00:36:22,514 --> 00:36:25,516
We need to put you in front
of the camera more often, baby.

609
00:36:25,517 --> 00:36:28,552
Kane, after you left,
he told Frank:

610
00:36:28,553 --> 00:36:29,953
"Not a good start for you."

611
00:36:29,954 --> 00:36:30,921
What does that mean?

612
00:36:30,922 --> 00:36:32,823
"Not a good start," what?

613
00:36:32,824 --> 00:36:34,758
"Not a good start for you."

614
00:36:34,759 --> 00:36:36,560
Do you have any idea
what that means?

615
00:36:36,561 --> 00:36:37,795
No, look,
he was in there.

616
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:44,902
What the fuck
does he want now?

617
00:36:44,903 --> 00:36:46,837
He says to gather
what you can from your bags

618
00:36:46,838 --> 00:36:47,905
to cover these windows.

619
00:36:47,906 --> 00:36:50,841
Why?

620
00:36:50,842 --> 00:36:52,443
And close the ones
with shades.

621
00:36:52,444 --> 00:36:54,678
Whatever it is,
let's just...

622
00:36:54,679 --> 00:36:56,647
Whoa, take it easy.

623
00:36:56,648 --> 00:36:58,982
We're covering the windows,
just doing what you're saying.

624
00:36:58,983 --> 00:37:01,985
He said
they need her up front.

625
00:37:09,928 --> 00:37:11,929
This is Juliana.

626
00:37:33,618 --> 00:37:36,620
Kane, I've got an idea.

627
00:37:58,776 --> 00:38:00,844
Hey!

628
00:38:05,717 --> 00:38:08,519
We're not scavengers.

629
00:38:08,520 --> 00:38:09,853
Carry on.

630
00:38:17,328 --> 00:38:18,729
Juliana...

631
00:38:18,730 --> 00:38:20,998
does this man frighten you?

632
00:38:24,602 --> 00:38:27,304
Is that a trick question?

633
00:38:27,305 --> 00:38:31,475
Would he frighten you more
if he were a religious fanatic

634
00:38:31,476 --> 00:38:34,478
or just a hijacker
holding us for ransom?

635
00:38:34,479 --> 00:38:35,879
Can he see what I'm doing?

636
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:38,882
He doesn't have a clue,
just keep going.

637
00:38:38,883 --> 00:38:39,850
I...I...I don't know.

638
00:38:43,855 --> 00:38:45,589
Let me restate.

639
00:38:45,590 --> 00:38:49,326
Does it make a difference?

640
00:38:49,327 --> 00:38:52,596
I got the N and the O.

641
00:39:00,772 --> 00:39:03,774
Yeah.

642
00:39:03,775 --> 00:39:07,044
Yeah, I think
there is a difference.

643
00:39:07,045 --> 00:39:09,079
I can rely on money
to come and save us

644
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:12,382
but I'm not certain
about God.

645
00:39:15,019 --> 00:39:18,021
- You may go.
- Thank you, Jul.

646
00:39:18,022 --> 00:39:19,623
Be safe.

647
00:39:19,624 --> 00:39:21,625
Thank you.

648
00:39:29,901 --> 00:39:30,500
Make sure you pull the shirts
tall so they can read it.

649
00:39:33,004 --> 00:39:34,871
Marcela, they want you next.

650
00:39:41,012 --> 00:39:44,014
Kane and Juliana are fine,
you'll be fine.

651
00:39:47,885 --> 00:39:49,886
Fuck!

652
00:39:54,459 --> 00:39:55,993
The skinny kid
is getting nosy.

653
00:39:55,994 --> 00:39:56,860
- How are we doing?
- Almost there.

654
00:39:59,097 --> 00:40:00,998
Frank, my turn.

655
00:40:03,134 --> 00:40:06,403
- Do you want me...?
- Please.

656
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:18,548
What the fuck are they doing?
She's been up there too long.

657
00:40:18,549 --> 00:40:20,817
Do you believe this?

658
00:40:20,818 --> 00:40:23,086
- That's great.
- I know.

659
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:25,956
He gave it back?

660
00:40:25,957 --> 00:40:28,692
What would frighten you more,

661
00:40:28,693 --> 00:40:30,160
a loud bang
or a quiet noise?

662
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:41,738
It's going to be okay,
just answer the question.

663
00:40:42,907 --> 00:40:45,809
I guess...

664
00:40:47,845 --> 00:40:49,980
the bang is scarier,

665
00:40:49,981 --> 00:40:50,614
but a quiet noise
is creepier.

666
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:58,689
So a poised person
whispering in your ear

667
00:40:58,690 --> 00:40:59,856
can be just as terrifying
as a lunatic howling?

668
00:41:03,127 --> 00:41:04,528
- In different ways.
- Listen...

669
00:41:06,564 --> 00:41:09,466
Would it frighten you more
if I were a raving madman

670
00:41:09,467 --> 00:41:12,002
threatening to blow up
this plane in the name of God,

671
00:41:12,003 --> 00:41:14,538
or if I calmly had a gun
pointing to your head

672
00:41:14,539 --> 00:41:18,875
while waiting to collect
my money?

673
00:41:18,876 --> 00:41:21,878
Just answer the question.

674
00:41:25,750 --> 00:41:28,752
I guess it doesn't matter.

675
00:41:31,155 --> 00:41:32,089
I wouldn't want to be
in either situation.

676
00:41:39,030 --> 00:41:42,032
That is understandable.

677
00:41:42,033 --> 00:41:44,901
Thank you, Marcela,
that is all.

678
00:41:48,172 --> 00:41:50,040
ANC wants a live report.

679
00:41:50,041 --> 00:41:52,175
I'm not a reporter;
I wouldn't know what to say.

680
00:41:52,176 --> 00:41:54,511
You'll say what you see,
it's very easy.

681
00:41:55,847 --> 00:41:57,848
What is that?

682
00:42:00,651 --> 00:42:02,185
Something in the window.

683
00:42:02,186 --> 00:42:04,187
Hold on.

684
00:42:09,794 --> 00:42:11,995
"No bomb."

685
00:42:11,996 --> 00:42:13,864
What's going on up there?
If she's not back in a minute...

686
00:42:16,534 --> 00:42:20,303
He asked for you to come.
Frank asked you to come.

687
00:42:20,304 --> 00:42:21,772
Pete...

688
00:42:21,773 --> 00:42:23,707
Give it to me,
I'll take it.

689
00:42:23,708 --> 00:42:26,676
Pete, there's something
about the question.

690
00:42:26,677 --> 00:42:27,711
You do realize
the consequences

691
00:42:29,580 --> 00:42:33,116
if this boy
doesn't agree with you?

692
00:42:33,117 --> 00:42:36,253
It's your rules.

693
00:42:36,254 --> 00:42:38,722
It's your opinion.

694
00:42:41,793 --> 00:42:43,994
Pete, sit down.

695
00:42:57,008 --> 00:42:59,609
What kind of questions
did he ask you?

696
00:42:59,610 --> 00:43:00,811
He asked me something
about a loud noise.

697
00:43:05,049 --> 00:43:06,283
Something about God.

698
00:43:06,284 --> 00:43:07,884
Did he ask you
anything about God?

699
00:43:07,885 --> 00:43:08,051
Something about what makes
you more fearful.

700
00:43:12,190 --> 00:43:13,657
God or money.

701
00:43:13,658 --> 00:43:15,992
- Money, yes.
- God or money.

702
00:43:15,993 --> 00:43:17,928
I think they're both
pretty terrifying.

703
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:24,868
Take your time.

704
00:43:35,646 --> 00:43:39,049
I don't care
why you're doing this.

705
00:43:39,050 --> 00:43:41,318
So whether I'm doing this
for religion or money,

706
00:43:41,319 --> 00:43:44,788
it does not influence
how much you fear me.

707
00:43:49,360 --> 00:43:51,828
No...

708
00:43:51,829 --> 00:43:54,831
It is the same end result.

709
00:43:59,303 --> 00:44:01,905
Frank...

710
00:44:01,906 --> 00:44:04,174
are you okay?

711
00:44:04,175 --> 00:44:05,909
Frank, what is going on?

712
00:44:05,910 --> 00:44:08,912
Just tell me.

713
00:44:08,913 --> 00:44:09,312
Just tell...

714
00:44:24,061 --> 00:44:28,665
Fear is fear, Frank.

715
00:44:32,236 --> 00:44:33,703
All right, okay.

716
00:44:33,704 --> 00:44:35,705
Jesus!

717
00:44:40,978 --> 00:44:42,846
Well, I lost.

718
00:44:42,847 --> 00:44:44,314
So you're going
to kill me then.

719
00:44:44,315 --> 00:44:47,851
Just like that.
No more interview.

720
00:44:47,852 --> 00:44:49,452
If that is
your only question,

721
00:44:49,453 --> 00:44:49,786
then you have missed
the point entirely.

722
00:44:52,757 --> 00:44:54,057
Is anything happening?

723
00:44:55,927 --> 00:44:58,795
Juliana, does anything
seem to be happening?

724
00:44:58,796 --> 00:45:01,798
No, but the side of the plane
looks like Wheel of Fortune.

725
00:45:01,799 --> 00:45:05,335
Shit, maybe we should have
spelled it in French.

726
00:45:05,336 --> 00:45:08,071
Frank is still up there.

727
00:45:08,072 --> 00:45:09,806
Is the military
doing anything?

728
00:45:09,807 --> 00:45:11,074
Nothing.

729
00:45:11,075 --> 00:45:12,008
- Are you sure?
- There's nothing!

730
00:45:14,178 --> 00:45:16,212
We're ready to go.

731
00:45:17,949 --> 00:45:20,216
Yeah, he's in here.

732
00:45:20,217 --> 00:45:21,251
I'll put him on.

733
00:45:42,206 --> 00:45:44,074
Okay...

734
00:45:44,075 --> 00:45:46,276
Say bye.

735
00:45:52,750 --> 00:45:55,085
Your name, Atlas, that's got
to stand for something,

736
00:45:55,086 --> 00:45:56,486
you know,
I was thinking...

737
00:45:56,487 --> 00:45:58,989
it kind of reminds me
of...

738
00:45:58,990 --> 00:46:00,390
Please...

739
00:46:00,391 --> 00:46:02,125
Please don't.

740
00:46:02,126 --> 00:46:03,960
You see...

741
00:46:03,961 --> 00:46:07,831
the omission
of the word "terrorist"

742
00:46:07,832 --> 00:46:09,499
is not the only thing
I disapproved of

743
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:11,968
in that network piece.

744
00:46:11,969 --> 00:46:16,506
I also hated its arrogance.

745
00:46:16,507 --> 00:46:19,376
They pretended to understand
that boy who was captured.

746
00:46:19,377 --> 00:46:21,511
Listing his choices,
talking about his family

747
00:46:21,512 --> 00:46:22,979
like they knew him.

748
00:46:22,980 --> 00:46:24,247
They don't know him.

749
00:46:24,248 --> 00:46:25,115
I get it, I get it.

750
00:46:25,116 --> 00:46:27,117
No, no, no,
you don't.

751
00:46:27,118 --> 00:46:28,351
I hated the piece too.

752
00:46:28,352 --> 00:46:30,053
So what,
you would have fixed it?

753
00:46:30,054 --> 00:46:31,921
I know more about your plight
than you think I do.

754
00:46:31,922 --> 00:46:33,189
- Oh, do you?
- Yes.

755
00:46:33,190 --> 00:46:37,794
I've been to Somalia
many times.

756
00:46:37,795 --> 00:46:39,129
I've actually been reading up

757
00:46:39,130 --> 00:46:42,265
on that kid on trial,
Mateo Wal-i-Musi.

758
00:46:42,266 --> 00:46:44,067
The one that you're
always talking about,

759
00:46:44,068 --> 00:46:45,902
you know, the angle
that I would have used...

760
00:46:45,903 --> 00:46:47,504
Stand up, Frank.

761
00:46:47,505 --> 00:46:49,973
- The angle I...
- Stand up, Frank!

762
00:46:49,974 --> 00:46:53,510
Did you hear that?
What that fuck?

763
00:46:53,511 --> 00:46:54,978
It's the pilot.

764
00:46:54,979 --> 00:46:57,213
They're doing something
to the pilot.

765
00:46:57,214 --> 00:46:58,248
Kneel down.

766
00:47:06,524 --> 00:47:08,591
Pretend with me, Frank,
that you are a young Somali.

767
00:47:13,330 --> 00:47:14,597
Say it.

768
00:47:14,598 --> 00:47:15,899
Say what?

769
00:47:15,900 --> 00:47:18,034
"I am a young Somali."

770
00:47:20,371 --> 00:47:22,038
I am a young Somali.

771
00:47:22,039 --> 00:47:24,908
According to your network,
you are doomed to die

772
00:47:24,909 --> 00:47:28,311
because you lost a game
of chance called privilege.

773
00:47:28,312 --> 00:47:31,314
But,
just at the last moment,

774
00:47:31,315 --> 00:47:34,050
someone gives you
another chance.

775
00:47:34,051 --> 00:47:36,920
They tell you
that if you take the knife,

776
00:47:36,921 --> 00:47:38,321
you will be spared.

777
00:47:38,322 --> 00:47:39,456
Take the knife, Frank.

778
00:47:41,192 --> 00:47:44,194
Take the knife, Frank!

779
00:47:44,195 --> 00:47:45,929
Now, of course,

780
00:47:45,930 --> 00:47:49,599
just taking the knife
is not enough.

781
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:51,201
- You have to use it.
- No.

782
00:47:51,202 --> 00:47:53,470
I want you to stab
this man right here.

