Good evening.

1296
01:25:11,607 --> 01:25:13,474
Today marks
the one-year anniversary

1297
01:25:13,475 --> 01:25:16,611
of the deadly hijacking
of Nairobi 86.

1298
01:25:16,612 --> 01:25:18,746
A tragedy that killed
nine people,

1299
01:25:18,747 --> 01:25:22,216
including four of our fellow
ANC employees.

1300
01:25:22,217 --> 01:25:22,617
Kane Lamprey,

1301
01:25:24,319 --> 01:25:26,754
Juliana Christensen,

1302
01:25:26,755 --> 01:25:28,723
Marcela Descalso,

1303
01:25:28,724 --> 01:25:31,492
and of course,
Frank Saltzman,

1304
01:25:31,493 --> 01:25:34,495
an American news icon.

1305
01:25:36,598 --> 01:25:38,332
Even a year later,

1306
01:25:38,333 --> 01:25:41,235
investigators continue to make
shocking discoveries,

1307
01:25:41,236 --> 01:25:43,437
after sifting through hours
of footage recovered

1308
01:25:43,438 --> 01:25:47,441
from cameras
on board the plane.

1309
01:25:47,442 --> 01:25:50,578
Each new revelation
has sparked a media frenzy.

1310
01:25:50,579 --> 01:25:52,446
But has it
also played a part

1311
01:25:52,447 --> 01:25:54,582
in the recent decision
to throw out the case

1312
01:25:54,583 --> 01:25:58,319
against alleged pirate
Mateo Wal-i-Musi?

1313
01:25:58,320 --> 01:26:00,187
And will it have
a similar effect

1314
01:26:00,188 --> 01:26:00,755
in the upcoming trial of
the young surviving hijacker?

1315
01:26:05,761 --> 01:26:07,928
Later in the hour we'll have
an exclusive interview

1316
01:26:07,929 --> 01:26:09,497
with Pete Bowers,

1317
01:26:09,498 --> 01:26:12,566
one of the only survivors
from that deadly day,

1318
01:26:12,567 --> 01:26:14,802
one year ago.

